arti airtel of india and ntt docomo inc of japan axiata holds  controlling stake in the entity bharti holds  while the remaining  is held by ntt docomo of japan sri lankaedit main article airtel sri lanka bharti airtel lanka pvt ltd is a subsidiary of bharti airtel limited bharti airtel has been featured in forbes asias fab  list rated amongst the best performing companies in the world in the businessweek it  list  and voted as indias most innovative company in a survey by the wall street journalcitation needed airtel lanka commenced commercial operations of services on  january  granted a licence in  in accordance with the sri lanka telecommunications act no  of  it is also a registered company under the board of investment sri lanka under the license the company provides digital mobile services to sri lanka this is inclusive of voice telephony voice mail data services and gsmbased services all of these services are provided under the airtel brand channel islands jersey and guernseyedit main article airtelvodafone on  may  jersey airtel and guernsey airtel both wholly owned subsidiaries of the bharti group announced they would launch mobile services in the british crown dependency islands of jersey and guernsey under the brand name airtelvodafone after signing an agreement with vodafone airtelvodafone operates a g network in jersey and guernsey subscriber baseedit bharti airtel has about  million subscribers worldwide— million in india and south asia and  million in africa as of the end of december  the numbers include mobile services subscribers in  countries and indian telemedia services and digital services subscribers one networkedit one network is a mobile phone network that allows airtel customers to use the service in a number of countries at the same price as their home network customers can place outgoing calls at the same rate as their local network and incoming calls are free as of update the service is available in bangladesh burkina faso chad democratic republic of congo congo brazzaville gabon ghana india kenya madagascar niger nigeria rwanda seychelles sierra leone sri lanka tanzania uganda and zambia only for international roamers from airtel africa acquisitions and mergersedit mtn group merger negotiationsedit in may  it emerged that airtel was exploring the possibility of buying the mtn group a south africabased telecommunications company with operations in  countries in africa and the middle east the financial times reported that bharti was considering offering us billion for a  stake in mtn which would be the largest overseas acquisition ever by an indian firm however both sides emphasised the tentative nature of the talks the economist magazine noted if anything bharti would be marrying up as mtn had more subscribers higher revenues and broader geographic coverage however the talks fell apart as mtn group tried to reverse the negotiations by making bharti almost a subsidiary of the new company in may  airtel confirmed that it was again in talks with mtn and both companies agreed to discuss the potential transaction exclusively by  july  airtel said bharti airtel ltd is pleased to announce that it has renewed its effort for a significant partnership with mtn group the exclusivity period was extended twice up to  september  talks eventually ended without agreement a solution was proposed where the new company would be listed on  stock exchanges one in south africa and one in india however duallisting of companies is not permitted by indian law zainedit further information zain group in jun  bharti struck a deal to buy zains mobile operations in  african countries in indias second biggest overseas acquisition after tata steels  billion buy of corus in  bharti airtel completed its  billion acquisition of african operations from kuwaiti firm on  june  making the airtel the worlds fifth largest wireless carrier by subscriber base airtel has reported that its revenues for the fourth quarter of  grew by  to us billion compared to the previous year newly acquired zain africa division contributed us million to the total however net profits dropped by  from us million in  to us million  due to a us million increase in radio spectrum charges in india and an increase of us million in debt interestcitation needed warid bangladesh and robiedit further information warid bangladesh and robi in  warid telecom sold a majority  stake in the company to bharti airtel for us million the bangladesh telecommunication regulatory commission approved the deal on  january  bharti airtel limited took management control of the company and its board and rebranded the companys services under its own airtel brand from  december  warid telecom sold its remaining  share to bharti airtels singaporebased concern bharti airtel holdings pte limited in march  on  november  airtel bangladesh was merged into robi as a product brand of robi where robi axiata limited is the licensee of airtel brand in bangladesh robi is a joint venture between axiata group holding  bharti airtel holding  and ntt docomo inc holding  telecom seychellesedit on  august  bharti airtel announced that it would acquire  stake in telecom seychelles for us million taking its global presence to  countries telecom seychelles began operations in  and operates g fixed line ship to shore services satellite telephony among value added services like vsat and gateways for international traffic across the seychelles under the airtel brand the company has over  share of the mobile market of seychelles airtel announced plans to invest us million in its fixed and mobile telecoms network in the seychelles over three years whilst also participating in the seychelles east africa submarine cable seas project the us million seas project is aimed at improving the seychelles global connectivity by building a  km undersea highspeed link to dar es salaam in tanzania wireless business services private limitededit on  may  airtel announced an agreement to acquire a  stake in wireless business services private limited wbspl at an investment of ₹ billion us million wbspl was a joint venture founded by qualcomm and held bwa spectrum in the telecom circles of delhi haryana kerala and mumbai qualcomm had spent us billion to acquire bwa spectrum in those  circles the deal gave airtel a g presence in  circles on  july  airtel announced that it had acquired an additional  equity share capital making its stake  in all the four bwa entities of qualcomm thereby making them its subsidiaries on  october  airtel announced that it had acquired  percent equity shares of wbspl for an undisclosed sum making it a wholly owned subsidiary augere wirelessedit airtel purchased augere wireless broadband india private limited a company that owned g spectrum in the chhattisgarhmadhya pradesh circle for an undisclosed sum in december  the economic times estimated augeres spectrum to be worth ₹ billion us million on  february  airtel announced that the merger of augere wireless into bharti airtel limited had been completed telenor indiaedit on  january  the economic times reported that airtel had entered into discussions with telenor india to acquire the latter on  february  airtel announced that it had entered into a definitive agreement to acquire telenor as part of the deal airtel will acquire telenor indias assets and customers in all seven telecom circles that the latter operates in  andhra pradesh bihar maharashtra gujarat uttar pradesh east uttar pradesh west and assam airtel will gain  mhz spectrum in the  mhz band from the telenor acquisition business standard reported that it was a nocash deal but would cost airtel ₹ crore over a  year period due to spectrum licence payments tikona g spectrumedit on  march  airtel announced that it had entered an agreement with tikona digital networks pvt ltd to purchase the latters g spectrum for approximately ₹ crore the deal also includes tikonas  cellular sites in  circles tikona had purchased  mhz of g spectrum in the  mhz band in the  auctions in gujarat himachal pradesh uttar pradesh east uttar pradesh west and rajasthan for ₹ crore prior to the deal airtel did not hold any spectrum in the  mhz band in up east up west and rajasthan and held mhz each in gujarat and himachal pradesh joint ventures and agreementsedit airtelvodafoneedit main article airtelvodafone on  may  jersey airtel and guernsey airtel both wholly owned subsidiaries of the bharti group announced they would launch mobile services in the british crown dependency islands of jersey and guernsey under the brand name airtelvodafone after signing an agreement with vodafone airtelvodafone operates a g network in jersey and guernsey airtelericssonedit ain july  bharti signed a fiveyear agreement with ericsson who will manage and optimise airtels mobile networks in africa ericsson will modernise and upgrade airtels mobile networks in africa with the latest technology including its multi standard rbs  base station as part of the modernisation ericsson will also provide technology consulting network planning  design and network deployment ericsson has been the managed services and network technology partner in the asian operations rebrandingedit logo used by airtel till november  on  november  airtel rebranded itself in india in the first phase of a global rebranding strategy the company unveiled a new logo with airtel written in lower case designed by londonbased brand agency the brand union the new logo is the letter a in lowercase with airtel written in lowercase under the logo on  november  airtels africa operations were rebranded to airtel sri lanka followed on  november  and on  december  warid telecom rebranded to airtel in bangladesh sponsorshipedit on  may  airtel signed a major deal with manchester united as a result of the deal airtel gets the rights to broadcast the matches played by the team to its customers bharti airtel signed a fiveyear deal with espn star sports to become the title sponsor of the champions league twenty cricket tournament but now the deal is terminated and karbonn mobiles is sponsoring champions league twenty cricket airtel also signed a deal to be title sponsor the inaugural formula one indian grand prix during the  season airtel signed a deal to be title sponsor the ileague for – ileague signature tuneedit the signature tune of airtel is composed by indian musician a r rahman the tune became hugely popular and is the worlds most downloaded mobile music with over  million downloads a r rahman along with anu malik has reused the same tune in kannada movie titled love a new version of the song was released on  november  as part of the rebranding of the company this version too was composed by rahman himself green initiativeedit greentowers p programedit bharti infratel is the only telecom tower company which has installed almost  mwt of solar capacity on their network generating more than  million units of electricity every year the green towers p program is scoped for  tower sites primarily rural areas having low or no grid power availability out of which  sites have already been implemented in the first year as a part of this year program once completed the initiative will reduce diesel consumption by  million litres per year with a significant carbon dioxide reduction of around  mt per year bharti infratel received the  green mobile award  at the gsma mobile world congress at barcelona and was also awarded the  innovative infrastructure company of the year award at the cnbc infrastructure awards for this groundbreaking initiative bharti remains the first company in the world to introduce the practice of sharing of passive infrastructure by collaborating with their competition to share mobile towers and to reduce the collective carbon footprint of the industrycitation needed this has become a subject of case studies in institutions including the harvard business schoolcitation needed energy conservationedit the company has installed solar hot water generator at its main campus in gurgaon for fulfilling the hot water requirement in the cafeteria majority of its facilities across ncr region are now equipped with les lighting energy savers which have reduced energy consumption in the lighting system to the tune of – variable frequency drives installed in the air handling unit at its campus have helped in enhancing the efficiency of cooling system by  these measures have resulted in a total saving of  units of electricity per year airtel has embarked upon technology related initiatives like virtualisation of servers that has helped it release over  cpus also the drive of sending ebills to the postpaid customers is helping save  trees annually within its campus the secure print solution—an automated queue managementbased secured printing solution has led to an annualised saving of about  metric tonnes of paper alternative energy sources such as solar energy used at  sites saving  million litres of diesel and approximately ₹ million us million energy efficiency measures such as integrated power management systems and variable speed dc generators have resulted in reduction in the rate of diesel consumption by  million liters leading to savings of ₹ million us across  sites demand side management like free cooling units instead of air conditioners has been implemented across  sites saving consumption of  million liters of diesel controversiesedit net neutrality debateedit for more details on this topic see net neutrality in india in february  gopal vittal ceo of airtels india operations said that companies offering free messaging apps like skype line and whatsapp should be regulated similar to telecom operators in august  trai rejected a proposal from telecom companies to make messaging application firms share part of their revenue with the carriers or the government in november  trai began investigating if airtel was implementing preferential access by offering special internet packs which allowed whatsapp and facebook data at rates which were lower than its standard data rates the statements of chua sock koong group ceo of singtel and also shareholder  of bharti airtel share similar statements about the antinet neutrality position in december  airtel changed its service terms for g and g data packs so that voip data was excluded from the set amount of free data a standard data charge of  paise ¢ us per  kb for g service and  paise ¢ us per  kb more than ₹ us for gb for g service was levied on voip data a few days later airtel announced a separated internet pack for voip apps it offered  mb for ₹ us with a validity of  days the trai chief rahul khullar said that airtel cannot be held responsible for violating net neutrality because india has no regulation that demands net neutrality airtels move faced criticism on social networking sites like facebook twitter and reddit later on  december  airtel announced that it would not be implementing planned changes pointing out that there were reports that trai would be soon releasing a consultation paper on the issue in april  airtel announced the airtel zero scheme under the scheme app firms will sign a contract and airtel will provide the apps for free to its customers the reports of flipkart an ecommerce firm joining the airtel zero scheme drew negative response people began to give the onestar rating to its app on google play following the protest flipkart decided to pull out of airtel zero the ecommerce giant confirmed the news in an official statement saying we will be walking away from the ongoing discussions with airtel for their platform airtel zero in october  indias telecom regulator trai recommended imposing a combined penalty of rs  crore on three mobile network operators — vodafone bharti airtel and idea cellular — for denying interconnection to mukesh ambani’s reliance jio infocomm rjio the latest entrant into india’s telecom service user privacyedit in june  a code used by the company was accused of compromising subscribers privacy see alsoedit bharti enterprises airtel india airtel africa airtel bangladesh airtel sri lanka airtelvodafone airtel digital tv airtel indian grand prix airtel delhi half marathon list of mobile network operators jio companies portal telecommunication portal referencesedit  a b overview airtelin retrieved  november    a b c d e bharti airtel financial statements  bharti airtel ltd   bharti airtel number of employees  bhartiartns calcutta macroaxiscom retrieved  november    shareholding pattern  bharti airtel airtelin archived from the original on  may  retrieved  june    shareholding pattern as of dec  bharti airtel pdf archived from the original pdf on  august  retrieved  june    airtel plans to launch its g volte services later this year says ceo ndtv gadgetscom retrieved    telecom subscription data june  pdf trai retrieved  october    airtel becomes third largest globally ndtv  june    hdfc bank named indias most valuable brand in brandz ranking   joji thomas philip  october  bharti airtel may merge india  africa operations by mid  – economic times economictimesindiatimescom retrieved  october    businessincom businessincom retrieved  august    hbr telecoms competitive solution outsourcing blogshbrorg retrieved  may    first break all the rules the economist  april  archived from the original on  may  retrieved  august    economistcom the economist  april  archived from the original on  may  retrieved  august    a b c sunil mittal timesnow interview youtubecom retrieved  april    a b nair vinod  december  sunil mittal speaking i started with a dream times of india   airtel completes  years of its hello tune service telecomtalkinfo  july  retrieved  november    emergingmarket telecoms eyes on africa the economist  may  retrieved  april    heather timmons  may   billion telecom deal falls apart new york times retrieved  april    james middleton  october  bharti and mtn have called off merger discussions once again telecomscom retriev